President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed sadness over the death of the pioneer Managing Director of the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), Festus Marinho. Marinho passed away recently. He was 87 years old. The expert was the first and only MD of the defunct Nigerian National Oil Corporation (NNOC). Buhari, in a letter to the Marinho family, described the deceased as a skilled and knowledgeable person. The President recalled working with him as Petroleum Minister for over three years. “He was brought back under my time as military head of state. I found him resourceful and hard-working.” The Nigerian leader prayed that God would rest Marinho’s soul and comfort the family.